Problem Statement: Given a string s and an integer k.Find the length of the longest substring with at most k distinct characters

Examples

Input :s = "aababbcaacc" , k = 2
Output :6
Explanation :The longest substring with at most two distinct characters is "aababb".
The length of the string 6


Input : s = "abcddefg" , k = 3
Output : 4
Explanation : The longest substring with at most three distinct characters is "bcdd".
The length of the string 4.



Longest Substring with K Uniques: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/longest-k-unique-characters-substring0853/1

class Solution {
    public int longestKSubstr(String s, int k) {
         int l = 0;
        int r = 0;
        int n = s.length();
        Map<Character, Integer> hm = new HashMap<>();
        int maxi = -1;

        while (r < n) {
            hm.put(s.charAt(r), r); // store latest index of each character
            if(hm.size()==k)
                maxi = Math.max(maxi, r - l + 1);
            else if (hm.size() > k) {
                int min = Collections.min(hm.values()); // find character with earliest index
                hm.remove(s.charAt(min)); // remove that character
                l = min + 1; // move left beyond removed character
                maxi = Math.max(maxi, r - l + 1);
            }
            r++;
        }

        return maxi;
    }
}
}
